'''Elliot Karl Stroud''' (born 22 June 2002) is a Swedish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a midfielder for [[Allsvenskan]] club [[Mjällby AIF]]<ref name="SW">{{soccerway|elliot-stroud/615454|access-date=9 October 2023}}</ref> and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

==Club career==
Stroud started his youth career in [[IK Oddevold]], joining the senior team in 2019. The club then suffered relegation to [[Division 2 (Swedish football)|Division 2]], the fourth tier of Swedish football, but bounced back to compete in the [[2022 Ettan]].<ref name=FT/><ref name=SW/> ''[[Expressen]]'' named Stroud as Oddevold's talent to watch out for in 2022.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/ettan/en-kopia-av-james-milner-i-liverpool/|author=Lund, Oskar|title="En kopia av James Milner i Liverpool"|date=1 April 2022|work=Expressen|language=sv|access-date=9 October 2023}}</ref> ''[[Aftonbladet]]'' included him on their top 30 list in the division, regardless of age.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/4oo6AG/30-basta-spelarna-i-ettan-fotbollen-2022-han-ar-bast|title=Rankar: 30 bästa spelarna i division 1-fotbollen 2022|date=29 October 2022 |language=sv|access-date=11 October 2023}}</ref>

Following a good season, Stroud had several offers from clubs higher in the division system.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bohuslaningen.se/sport/fotboll/oddevolds-elliot-stroud-om-framtiden-ett-viktigt-beslut-som-far-ta-tid.b2e64cec-ec5d-47e3-ae25-07f4fb4007e5|title=Oddevolds Elliot Stroud om framtiden: "Ett viktigt beslut som får ta tid"|work=Bohusläningen|date=|language=sv|access-date=9 October 2023}}</ref> He chose [[Mjällby AIF]] and signed a contract until 2025.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/allsvenskan/klart-stroud-till-mjallby/|title=Klart: Stroud till Mjällby|date=8 December 2022|author=Billengren, Ludwig|publisher=Fotbollskanalen|language=sv|access-date=9 October 2023}}</ref> He made his [[Allsvenskan]] debut in April 2023 against [[Degerfors IF|Degerfors]].<ref name=SW/>

==International career==
In March 2026, Stroud received his first call-up to the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]] for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification second round]] games against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] and [[Poland national football team|Poland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2026/03/herrtrupp-playoff/|title=God mix i Graham Potters marstrupp|trans-title=Good mix in Graham Potter's march squad|language=Swedish|publisher=[[Swedish Football Association]]|date=18 March 2025|access-date=18 March 2025}}</ref> On 12 May 2026, he was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Mystiskt inlägg efter petningen |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm-2026/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.expressen.se |language=sv}}</ref> Stroud made his full international debut for Sweden on 4 June 2026 in a [[Friendly game|friendly]] 2–2 draw with [[Greece national football team|Greece]], replacing [[Gabriel Gudmundsson]] in the 66th minute.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sweden vs. Greece |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/sverige-grekland-landskamper-herr-senior/6822861/ |website=SvFF}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Stroud's brother Adam is also a professional footballer who plays for [[IF Brommapojkarna|Brommapojkarna]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sverigesradio.se/artikel/tva-broder-stroud-i-allsvenskan-kommer-ta-hjalp-av-brorsan|title=Två bröder Stroud i allsvenskan: ”Kommer ta hjälp av brorsan”|website=sverigesradio.se|date=21 June 2025|accessdate=25 March 2026|language=Swedish}}</ref> The pair have an English father.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fotbolldirekt.se/silly-season/avslojar-nya-intresset-for-stroud-och-guldbiljetten-till-england/|title=AVSLÖJAR: Nya intresset för Stroud – och ”guldbiljetten” till England|website=fotbolldirekt.se|date=4 November 2025|accessdate=25 March 2026|language=Swedish}}</ref>

